abstract = {The intensification of competition in the global market and the increase in the demand for personalized customization have put forward higher requirements for the development cycle, production quality and service quality of complex products. By coordinating the data in the two stages of design and operation, this work creates a common method for information integration in different lifecycle stages, which helps to enhance the value of enterprises. Combined with the new generation of information technologies such as industrial Internet, sensor technology and industrial software, a modular design model based on operation feedback is proposed, which helps enterprises to allocate manufacturing resources and design solutions based on market feedback in the design stage, so as to solve the problems of delayed product lifecycle information interaction, low collaboration efficiency, slow response to market changes, etc. A case of a circulating water pump is also analyzed to verify the feasibility of the proposed model in promoting lifecycle information collaboration, and the results show that through the reliability analysis based on operation, the model can reduce the cost by 930,000 yuan on the basis of satisfying the requirements of each sub-system. In summary, the model performs collaborative optimization on the basis of integrating design and operation data, which can promote the improvement of enterprise benefits.},
